<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN266-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – pāṭāṇṭiṇai. tuṟai – paricilkaṭānilai. cōḻaṉ uruvappaḵṟēr iḷañcēṭceṉṉiyaip peruṅkuṉṟūr kiḻār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN266">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>payaṅkeḻu māmaḻai peyyātu māṟik</l>
<l>kayaṅkaḷi muḷiyuṅ kōṭai yāyiṉum</l>
<l>puḻaṟkā lāmpa lakalaṭai nīḻaṟ</l>
<l>katirkōṭu nantiṉ curimuka vēṟṟai</l>
<l>nākiḷa vaḷaiyoṭu pakaṉmaṇam pukūu</l>
<l>nīrtikaḻ kaḻaṉi nāṭukeḻu peruviṟal</l>
<l>vāṉṟōy nīḷkuṭai vayamāṉ ceṉṉi</l>
<l>cāṉṟō rirunta vavaiyat tuṟṟō</l>
<l>ṉācā keṉṉum pūcal pōla</l>
<l>vallē kaḷaimati yattai yuḷḷiya</l>
<l>viruntukaṇ ṭoḷikkun tiruntā vāḻkkaip</l>
<l>poṟippuṇa ruṭampiṟ ṟōṉṟiyeṉ</l>
<l>ṉaṟivukeṭa niṉṟa nalkūr maiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="6">With great victories over lands with water-glittering paddy fields, </l>
<l corresp="4">where the curly-faced male snail with ear[-shaped] feelers </l>
<l corresp="5">enters into daytime union with the young sea-snail conch </l>
<l corresp="3">in the shade of the wide leaves of tube-stemmed white waterlilies </l>
<l corresp="2">even though the west wind dries the silt by the pond </l>
<l corresp="1">after the well-filled dark clouds changed [position] without raining, </l>
<l>Oh top [man] on the strong animal with a sky-touchig tall parasol (7),</l>
<l corresp="9">resembling the clamour that says “may he be a support, </l>
<l corresp="8">to the one who experiences [his] assembly where worthy men sit”, </l>
<l corresp="10a-c">may you remove [it] fast </l>
<l corresp="13">– the poverty that lasted so that my knowledge got lost, </l>
<l corresp="12">appearing with a body joined with the marks </l>
<l corresp="10d-11">of an imperfect living that will hide when seeing the feasts remembered. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
